   <body>
      <p>A set of tools in the document viewer enables you to view and inspect
            2D and 3D drawings in detail. The options and tools depend on the type of file you
            open.</p>
      <p>In general, after you select a tool, you can continue to use other
            tools along with it. For example, after you select<uicontrol>Explode Model</uicontrol>, you can use<uicontrol>Zoom</uicontrol>and<uicontrol>Orbit</uicontrol>tools. To restore your drawing
            model to the default view, click<uicontrol>Home</uicontrol>.</p>
      <p>The following table provides information on using each of the tools in
            the document viewer.</p>
      <p>
         <table colsep="1" rowsep="1">
            <tgroup cols="3">
               <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="20%"/>
               <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="20%"/>
               <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="60%"/>
               <thead>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Term</entry>
                     <entry>Icon</entry>
                     <entry>Function</entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Pan </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image4.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Pan</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>Drag to move the drawing or model to a
                                different part of the viewer. </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Zoom </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image5.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Zoom</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>Perform any of the following options to
                                zoom in or zoom out a drawing model: <ul>
                           <li>Click a part of the design and
                                        double-click to zoom. </li>
                           <li>Click a part of the design and press
                                        CTRL + Down Arrow key to zoom in and CTRL + Up Arrow key to
                                        zoom out. </li>
                           <li>Click a part of the design and rotate
                                        the wheel button. <ul>
                                 <li>Forward or away from user = zoom
                                                out. </li>
                                 <li>Backward or towards the user =
                                                zoom in. </li>
                              </ul>
                           </li>
                           <li>Click <uicontrol>Home </uicontrol>to
                                        return to the default view. </li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Camera Interactions </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image17.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Camera Interactions</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image17.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Camera Interactions</alt>
                        </image> and then click the type of view you want to use. <ul>
                           <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image18.png" placement="inline">
                                 <alt>Fit to view</alt>
                              </image> to position the model at the center of the
                                        viewport. </li>
                           <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image19.png" placement="inline">
                                 <alt>Roll</alt>
                              </image> to rotate the model. </li>
                           <li>If the file is a 3D model, then click
                                            <image href="../../Icons/FV-image20.png" placement="inline">
                                 <alt>Adjust Focal length</alt>
                              </image> to change the current camera focal length of the
                                        model. </li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Measure </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image7.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Measure</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>Click to view all the measurement options
                                and then select the appropriate option. When completed, click
                                    <uicontrol>Done</uicontrol>
                                to turn off the measurement. <p>In 2D designs,
                                    you can use the following measurement options:</p>
                        <ul>
                           <li>Distance</li>
                           <li>Angle</li>
                           <li>Area</li>
                           <li>Arc</li>
                           <li>Calibrate</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>In 3D designs, you can use the following
                                    measurement options:</p>
                        <ul>
                           <li>Distance</li>
                           <li>Angle</li>
                           <li>Calibrate</li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Document Browser </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image21.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Document Browser</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>To switch the view between 2D and 3D,
                                perform the following steps: <ol>
                           <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image21.png" placement="inline">
                                 <alt>Document Browser</alt>
                              </image>. <p>The <uicontrol>Document
                                                Browser</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p>
                           </li>
                           <li>In the <uicontrol>Tree </uicontrol>tab,
                                        expand <uicontrol>Model
                                        </uicontrol>and then click the appropriate view. <note> If the document supports only
                                                <uicontrol>2D
                                                View </uicontrol>, then the <uicontrol>3D View
                                            </uicontrol> option is not available. </note>
                           </li>
                           <li>To view the thumbnails of the drawing,
                                        click the <uicontrol>Thumbnails </uicontrol>tab. </li>
                           <li>Click the appropriate page. </li>
                        </ol>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Layer Manager </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image22.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Layer Manager</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>To view layers in the drawing design,
                                perform the following steps: <ol>
                           <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image22.png" placement="inline">
                                 <alt>Layer Manager</alt>
                              </image>. The <uicontrol>Layers </uicontrol>dialog box is displayed. </li>
                           <li>In the <uicontrol>Layers
                                        </uicontrol>dialog box, click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image23.png" placement="inline">
                                 <alt>Show/Hide </alt>
                              </image>to show or hide layers in the drawing model. <p>Alternatively, in the <uicontrol>Enter Filter
                                                Term</uicontrol> box, click and enter the layer name
                                            to search for a layer.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ol>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Properties </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image10.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Properties</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>Click to view the properties of a selected
                                part within the drawing. </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>Full Screen </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image11.png" placement="inline">
                           <alt>Full Screen</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>Click to change the viewer to full-screen
                                view. <p>Press <uicontrol>Esc</uicontrol> or click
                                    the <uicontrol>Full
                                        Screen</uicontrol> toggle option to exit full-screen
                                    view.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
      <section>
         <title>Tools specific to 3D drawings:</title>
         <p>
            <table colsep="1" rowsep="1">
               <tgroup cols="3">
                  <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="20%"/>
                  <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="20%"/>
                  <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="60%"/>
                  <thead>
                     <row>
                        <entry>Term</entry>
                        <entry>Icon</entry>
                        <entry>Function</entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                     <row>
                        <entry>Orbit </entry>
                        <entry>
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image24.png" placement="inline">
                              <alt>Orbit</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image24.png" placement="inline">
                              <alt>Orbit</alt>
                           </image> and then click the appropriate rotate option you want
                                    to use. <ul>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image25.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Rotate</alt>
                                 </image> to rotate the model. </li>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image26.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Rotate and Tilt</alt>
                                 </image> to rotate and tilt the model as needed. </li>
                           </ul>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>First Person </entry>
                        <entry>
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image27.png" placement="inline">
                              <alt>Navigate in first person</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>To navigate through the 3D drawing
                                    model as if you were actually inside the model, perform the
                                    following steps: <ol>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image27.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Navigate in first
                                                  person</alt>
                                 </image>. The <uicontrol>Navigate in First
                                                Person </uicontrol> dialog box is displayed. </li>
                              <li>Read the navigation instructions,
                                            and then click <uicontrol>Ok, Got It
                                            </uicontrol>. </li>
                              <li>Navigate through the 3D model using
                                            the following options: <ul>
                                    <li>Use the directional keys on
                                                  the keyboard to navigate through your model.
                                                  Alternatively, you can use the <uicontrol>W A S
                                                  D</uicontrol> keys as the directional keys. <ul>
                                          <li>↑ or W - move forward </li>
                                          <li>↓ or S - move back </li>
                                          <li>← or A - move left </li>
                                          <li>→ or D - move right </li>
                                       </ul>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>Use Shift + directional keys
                                                  to move faster. </li>
                                    <li>To adjust the walk speed,
                                                  use the + or - keys. </li>
                                    <li>Click <uicontrol>Home</uicontrol> to return to the default view.
                                                </li>
                                 </ul>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>Section Analysis </entry>
                        <entry>
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image28.png" placement="inline">
                              <alt>Section Analysis</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image28.png" placement="inline">
                              <alt>Section Analysis</alt>
                           </image> and then click the type of sectioning you want to use.
                                        <ul>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image29.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Section along x-axis</alt>
                                 </image> to section along the x-axis. </li>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image30.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Section along y-axis</alt>
                                 </image> to section along the y-axis. </li>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image31.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Section along z-axis</alt>
                                 </image> to section along the z-axis. </li>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image32.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Section a specific
                                                  area</alt>
                                 </image> to section a specific area. </li>
                           </ul>
                           <p>Drag the desired manipulators until the
                                        model is sectioned the way you want it. When done, click
                                            <image href="../../Icons/FV-image28.png" placement="inline">
                                 <alt>Section Analysis</alt>
                              </image> again to turn off sectioning.</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>Explode Model </entry>
                        <entry>
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image34.png" placement="inline">
                              <alt>Explode Model</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>To take apart a 3D drawing design and
                                    see the parts that make up the model, perform the following
                                    steps: <ol>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image34.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Explode Model</alt>
                                 </image>. A slider <image href="../../Icons/FV-image35.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Slider</alt>
                                 </image> is displayed. </li>
                              <li>Drag the slider forward to separate
                                            the parts of the model. </li>
                              <li>Drag the slider backward to bring
                                            the model back together. </li>
                              <li>Optionally, use <uicontrol>Zoom</uicontrol>
                                            to take a closer look at a part. </li>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image34.png" placement="inline"/> again to go back to the
                                            default view. </li>
                           </ol>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>Model Browser </entry>
                        <entry>
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image37.png" placement="inline">
                              <alt>Model Browser</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>To view or hide a model in the
                                    drawing, perform the following steps: <ol>
                              <li>Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image37.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Model Browser</alt>
                                 </image>. The <uicontrol>Model</uicontrol>
                                            dialog box is displayed. </li>
                              <li>In the <uicontrol>Model</uicontrol>
                                            dialog box, click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image23.png" placement="inline">
                                    <alt>Show/Hide</alt>
                                 </image> to show or hide a complete model or the parts
                                            in the drawing design. </li>
                              <li>In the <uicontrol>Search</uicontrol> box, click and enter the name of
                                            the part that you want to search. </li>
                           </ol>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
            </table>
         </p>
      </section>
   </body>
